{"TopicId":221442,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Suggested dv calculator improvements","CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T12:44:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T12:44:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo start: I LOVE the new \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E readout. But it can use a little more work:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. Make it so this \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, Burn, Start, automatically appears when expanding the tab. Now you have to click the \u0027expand stage\u0027 button twice to enable it, or use the settings icon, but ultimately, anyone who expands the stage wants to look at the stage in greater depth (including \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E info). No need to put that behind more clicks/settings\u003Cbr\u003E\nTwo clicks needed:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022LUkzZZk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002241.12\u0022 height=\u0022183\u0022 width=\u0022445\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LUkzZZk.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fjUajW5.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002239.19\u0022 height=\u0022145\u0022 width=\u0022370\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/fjUajW5.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. Leave the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E picker on the last celestial body you used, also when going out of the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003Evab\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and going back. Currently it just forgets, when replacing an engine with a new engine, you have to set the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E settings again.\u003Cbr\u003E\n3. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E numbers can be hard to read on a big screen. Use a clearer/bigger font\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u002217bqvkx.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/17bqvkx.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nFull resolution:\u003Cimg alt=\u0022iQeGYo3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002230.17\u0022 height=\u0022108\u0022 width=\u0022358\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/iQeGYo3.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow I see it on my screen:\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bCRiMov.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002229.89\u0022 height=\u002255\u0022 width=\u0022184\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/bCRiMov.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-03-19T13:43:02Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2024 01:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Mar 19\u0022\u003EMarch 19\u003C/time\u003E by Abelinoss\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Echanged discord for imgur links\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}